the original totem of the Tanais River Valley Amazons.<br>
<br>
At the mouth of the Tanais River stood a regal figure holding the reins of Hannibal. She wore familiar baggy buck skin pants with a rope of talismans wrapping around her waist, but she had one new piece, her buck skin bra-like top. This top allowed her skin to reveal its many tatoos. On the left breast, the brand of the Shaman; On the right arm, &quot;Amazon Queen&quot; in Ancient lettering; On the shoulder blade was a snow leopard. Ahh, but now a new tatoo inked her body, her left arm had a large indigo dragon coiling up her arms from wrist to shoulder, a stream of fire the creature spat wrapped around the base of Yakut's neck. Yakut wore her stagg antler headdress but her long brown tresses were now streaked wih thick gray strands. The Queen was jaded, and little bit more wrinkled but she was still alive.<br>
<br>
She mounted her steed and rode into her city, green orbs gleamed with pride as they saw the progress of her people. Yakut flung her leg over and slid from the saddle. She let go of Hannibal's reins and walked to the large platform, a crowd of Amazons followed her there cheering and whispering.<br>
<br>
