 She leaned back against a tree, her arms folded over her chest as she listened to snippits of conversation, then looked over at her mare, who was watching the women almost curiously. She smiled a bit, then looked back to the going's on.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3F3F3F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/bamazonsunite.showUserPublicProfile?gid=amazonqueenyakut>Amazon Queen Yakut </A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_fire.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Queen Shamaness</span><br>  Posts: 302<br> <font color=#6F6F6F>(4/11/03 10:39 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm29.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=88.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://members.aol.com/_ht_a/magickalamzn/images/yakut1.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Greetings...</span><hr size=1> Yakut sensed a newcomer not too far away, but the newcomer posed no threat and therfore the Shamaness merely shrugged away the feeling. Suddenly, her eyes were drawn to a overly familiar face. A smile displayed on her features as she still in tears stepped forward to greet her twin sister and nephew.<br>
<br>
The Amazon wrapped her quite opposite twin into a tight embrace, &quot;Oh by the Goddess, sister! I have missed you so!&quot; She slid from the embrace and smiled to Skylar.<br>
<br>
&quot;And how goes it my nephew?&quot;, she laughed caringly andgave him a kiss on the forehead. Yakut heard Otere's voice above the crowd and turned towards her as she spoke. When the other Amazons cheered, Yakut's face turned red from smiling too much, her cheeks began to ache but she didn't care! She had returned to her family, and home.<br>
